A former Minister of Commerce and Industry, Mahmud Tukur, is dead. He died on Friday in Abuja, one of his relations told Premium Times. SaharaReporters Media Apart from being a former Minister of Commerce and Industry during the military regime of General Buhari, Tukur was the first Vice Chancellor of Bayero University, Kano and also a former director of Cadbury Nigeria. Mr Tukur served as minister during the military government of Muhammadu Buhari. He is believed to have remained close to Mr Buhari, Nigeriaâ€™s current democratic president.